{
    "id": "sysadmin/resource-monitoring",
    "title": "Monitor System Resources",
    "description": "Track CPU, memory, and disk locally, then optionally level up to remote colony-node monitoring.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/linux_resource_monitoring_dashboard.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/orion.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Resource monitoring starts on your Ubuntu laptop: top, free, and df tell you where bottlenecks form before users notice.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "local-monitor",
                    "text": "Do local monitoring first"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "local-monitor",
            "text": "Run top -b -n 1 and df -h, save both to resource-snapshot.txt, and highlight one possible bottleneck. This is enough to complete today's mission.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "sysadmin-capture-local-resource-snapshot",
                    "text": "Capture local CPU/memory/disk snapshot"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "remote-brief",
                    "text": "Snapshot captured",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "d2f36c0a-7b90-4fdd-9ac5-3a66a2fbe4b2",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "remote-brief",
            "text": "Next level: Metaguild asks you to observe a remote colony node. Your laptop remains mission control, but a dedicated Raspberry Pi node simulates real multi-node operations. Optional now, essential later.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "process",
                    "process": "sysadmin-capture-remote-node-telemetry",
                    "text": "Optional: capture remote colony node telemetry"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-1",
                    "text": "Proceed to quiz"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-1",
            "text": "Which command is best for a live-updating process list sorted by CPU usage?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-2",
                    "text": "top"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "monitor-retry",
                    "text": "df -h"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "monitor-retry",
                    "text": "cat /etc/os-release"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-2",
            "text": "What does df -h primarily report?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-3",
                    "text": "Filesystem disk space in human-readable units"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "monitor-retry",
                    "text": "Per-process CPU percentages"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "monitor-retry",
                    "text": "Kernel ring buffer logs"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-3",
            "text": "If load spikes but disk is healthy, what should you inspect next?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "quiz-4",
                    "text": "CPU-heavy processes and memory pressure in top/free output"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "monitor-retry",
                    "text": "Only the desktop wallpaper settings"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "monitor-retry",
                    "text": "Nothing; monitoring is done"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quiz-4",
            "text": "Why practice on both laptop and Raspberry Pi node?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "Laptop skills transfer directly, and remote-node monitoring prepares you for distributed systems"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "monitor-retry",
                    "text": "Because local monitoring never works on Ubuntu laptops"
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "monitor-retry",
                    "text": "Because top and df require cluster hardware"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "monitor-retry",
            "text": "Close, but not quite. Re-run your snapshot process and review how each command maps to CPU, memory, or disk signals.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "local-monitor",
                    "text": "Retry monitoring path"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Great work. You can monitor a single Ubuntu machine now and understand why multi-node observability is the next frontier.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "Complete resource monitoring",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "d2f36c0a-7b90-4fdd-9ac5-3a66a2fbe4b2",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    "rewards": [
